Currently our S3 endpoints are IP locked to EC2 IPs. So the traffic cannot go through the user's VPN link (unless they later route it back to EC2 somehow). Inside a VPC, instances needing access to external resources will have to follow one of these routes:

# be assigned an EIP (in which case they can access external resources using AWS's infrastructure);
# be provided with a NAT host (in which case all of the traffic egresses the VPC via the user's own NAT);
# use the s3 endpoint (http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonVPC/latest/UserGuide/vpc-endpoints.html).

